    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>In Greek literature θεμέλιος (masc.) and θεμέλιον (neuter) occur in the meaning of ‘foundation,’ but in the NT θεμέλιον in the sense of ‘foundation’ happens to occur only in the plural form ({S:04401602600018}).</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>λίθος in the sense of ‘building stone’ (that is, a shaped stone in contrast with a field stone) is treated in Domain 2 Natural Substances ({D:2.24}).</Content>
    </Note>
